have such a
bad attitude about it.

308
00:18:13,125 --> 00:18:15,125
I mean, did they
have to be that rude?

309
00:18:15,208 --> 00:18:16,541
Can you believe
the condescending look

310
00:18:16,625 --> 00:18:18,125
that teller gave me?

311
00:18:18,208 --> 00:18:20,041
That ticked me off.

312
00:18:20,125 --> 00:18:21,583
So what if
they're a huge bank?!

313
00:18:21,666 --> 00:18:23,833
They can't treat
people like that.

314
00:18:23,916 --> 00:18:25,500
Just try not to
let it bother you.

315
00:18:25,583 --> 00:18:27,291
And I could have
used a little more help.

316
00:18:27,375 --> 00:18:29,375
I'm doing this
for you, you know?!

317
00:18:30,375 --> 00:18:31,583
Come on now.

318
00:18:31,666 --> 00:18:34,083
Let's just all try to
calm down a little bit.

319
00:18:34,166 --> 00:18:36,875
Oh, uh... Would you
mind paying for these?

320
00:18:38,083 --> 00:18:39,166
I guess.

321
00:18:39,250 --> 00:18:40,541
Yay!

322
00:18:40,625 --> 00:18:42,458
Kotaro! Get a
hold of yourself!

323
00:18:42,541 --> 00:18:44,875
You keep jumping like that this
whole boat's gonna turn over.

324
00:18:44,958 --> 00:18:46,125
Sorry.

325
00:18:47,041 --> 00:18:48,875
As you can see,
the float mart is kind of

326
00:18:48,958 --> 00:18:50,666
like the Old Yard's kitchen.

327
00:18:50,750 --> 00:18:53,083
You can get just
about anything here.

328
00:18:53,750 --> 00:18:56,083
Can we go in there?
Please, please?

329
00:18:56,166 --> 00:18:59,541
Sure thing. You guys feel
like grabbing some lunch?

330
00:18:59,625 --> 00:19:01,541
Jiro, are you
affected by garlic?

331
00:19:03,333 --> 00:19:04,750
Don't move.

332
00:19:06,166 --> 00:19:08,125
I think that they
have us surrounded.

333
00:19:09,041 --> 00:19:10,166
How'd they find us out here?

334
00:19:10,250 --> 00:19:12,750
Brother, are you okay?

335
00:19:19,541 --> 00:19:21,166
It seems that members
of the Darkness have come to

336
00:19:21,250 --> 00:19:23,250
welcome us to the Special Zone.

337
00:19:23,333 --> 00:19:24,666
Don't worry.

338
00:19:24,750 --> 00:19:26,583
They're not the most formidable
group I've come across.

339
00:19:26,666 --> 00:19:29,333
We'll just try to sidestep
them here and draw them away.

340
00:19:32,375 --> 00:19:35,666
Let's get outta here so
innocent people don't get hurt.

341
00:19:43,833 --> 00:19:45,958
Hey, Kotaro. You think
that you can follow me?

342
00:19:46,041 --> 00:19:47,458
Sure thing, brother.

343
00:19:47,541 --> 00:19:48,125
Let's go, then!

344
00:19:48,208 --> 00:19:49,875
Woo-hooo!

345
00:19:51,125 --> 00:19:52,875
We're really
sorry about the boat, sir!

346
00:19:52,958 --> 00:19:55,125
Just send the
bill to the Company.

347
00:20:00,625 --> 00:20:02,583
Can't you draw less
attention to yourself?

348
00:20:02,666 --> 00:20:04,125
That's not an option.

349
00:20:04,208 --> 00:20:07,583
My only concern is getting
you back onto dry land safely.

350
00:20:07,666 --> 00:20:10,291
I'm gonna be in so much trouble.

351
00:20:13,333 --> 00:20:15,958
Now I'll see what the
Silver Blade's capable of.

352
00:20:22,333 --> 00:20:25,166
How do I get myself
into these situations?

353
00:20:25,958 --> 00:20:28,625
Impressive. You managed
to dodge all our

354
00:20:28,708 --> 00:20:30,166
bullets out on the water.

355
00:20:30,250 --> 00:20:32,208
I'm sure that was tiring.

356
00:20:32,291 --> 00:20:35,708
What's wrong? Was that too
much of a work out for you?

357
00:20:35,791 --> 00:20:37,166
Oh, that little
bit of action was

358
00:20:37,250 --> 00:20:39,666
a piece of cake
for the legendary hero.

359
00:20:39,750 --> 00:20:41,208
No doubt about it.

360
00:20:41,291 --> 00:20:44,291
But now I've got you in my
sights, so don't make a move.

361
00:20:44,375 --> 00:20:47,791
Or there'll be a mountain of
bodies caught in the crosshairs.

362
00:20:48,541 --> 00:20:49,916
Why are you doing this?

363
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,416
Shut up, you company woman.

364
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:54,250
If I wanted to, I could
shoot you down right now.

365
00:20:56,041 --> 00:21:01,041
You can relax. We don't
on fighting anymore... today.

366
00:21:01,125 --> 00:21:03,583
However, if you
decide to take up

367
00:21:03,666 --> 00:21:05,958
residence here
